  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is the Script Tag?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The <script> tag is used to embed or link JavaScript in an HTML document to add interactivity and dynamic behavior."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Inline Script"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script>\n  alert('Hello World');\n</script>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "External Script"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script src=\"script.js\"></script>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Script Placement"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Scripts can be placed in the <head> or before the closing </body> tag. Placing scripts at the bottom improves page loading performance."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<body>\n  <h1>Hello</h1>\n  <script src=\"script.js\"></script>\n</body>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Async Attribute"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The async attribute loads the script asynchronously without blocking HTML parsing."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script src=\"script.js\" async></script>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Defer Attribute"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The defer attribute ensures the script executes after the HTML document is fully parsed."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script src=\"script.js\" defer></script>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Async vs Defer"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Feature", "Async", "Defer"],
        "rows": [
          ["Execution Time", "As soon as loaded", "After HTML parsing"],
          ["Order", "Not guaranteed", "Maintained order"],
          ["Blocking", "Non-blocking", "Non-blocking"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using type Attribute"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n  console.log('Hello');\n</script>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Module Scripts"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<script type=\"module\" src=\"app.js\"></script>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use external scripts for better maintainability**",
        "**Place scripts at the bottom or use defer**",
        "**Use async for independent scripts**",
        "**Minimize and optimize JavaScript files**",
        "**Avoid inline scripts in production**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Blocking page load with scripts in head**",
        "**Using async incorrectly for dependent scripts**",
        "**Mixing inline and external scripts unnecessarily**",
        "**Not optimizing script size**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The script tag enables dynamic behavior in web pages. Proper usage of async, defer, and external scripts improves performance and maintainability."
    }
  ],
  "faq": [
    {
      "question": "What does the script tag do?",
      "answer": "It is used to add JavaScript to HTML pages."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the difference between async and defer?",
      "answer": "Async executes immediately after loading, while defer waits until HTML parsing is complete."
    },
    {
      "question": "Where should scripts be placed?",
      "answer": "At the bottom of the body or using defer for better performance."
    }
